        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We will configure the correlator for our CO(2-1) observations
to be in dual-polarization mode with 3840 channels spanning 
a bandwith of 1875~MHz and a pre-smoothing factor of 4 to 
provide 2.5 km/s per channel. We request the most extended
configuration for the 12m array available in cycle 2 to resolve 
the smallest molecular structures possible (0.2" or 30 pc).  
This spatial resolution is comparable with the resolution of 
single dish observations of nearby galaxies.  With this resolution,
sytems larger than a few arcseconds will be reslved out, but
this scale is larger than the largest GMAs detected in our 
cycle 0 data. We require a mass sensitivity limit 4e4 Mo 
(at 3 sigma), comparable to Galactic GMCs. A molecular mass 
of 4e5 Mo at the distance of NGC 5044 (Dl=31.2 Mpc)
will produce an integrated line intensity in CO(2-1) of 
7.5 mJy km/s, assuming Xco=2e20. We therefore request a rms 
sensitivity of 1 mJy/beam/channel with channel width of 2.5 km/s
(a factor of 4 smoothing) to detect a 4e5 Mo cloud at 3 sigma.  
For cycle 2, we propose a mosaic of 12m array observations 
in CO(2-1) covering the central 5x5 kpc region which contains 
the brightest [CII] and Ha emission (see Fig. 7 in the 
scientific justification).  Based on the ALMA Observing Tool 
we can mosaic the central 5x5 kpc region to a sensitivity 
of 1 mJy/beam/channel, where a channel equals 
2.5 km/s in a total time (calibration plus overhead) of 5.7 hr.
</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
